{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":844,"text":"So this is a talk about gene drives,"},{"time":3330,"text":"but I'm going to start\nby telling you a brief story."},{"time":6621,"text":"20 years ago, a biologist\nnamed Anthony James"},{"time":9868,"text":"got obsessed with the idea\nof making mosquitos"},{"time":12211,"text":"that didn't transmit malaria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15683,"text":"It was a great idea,\nand pretty much a complete failure."},{"time":20596,"text":"For one thing, it turned out\nto be really hard"},{"time":23280,"text":"to make a malaria-resistant mosquito."},{"time":26286,"text":"James managed it, finally,\njust a few years ago,"},{"time":29937,"text":"by adding some genes\nthat make it impossible"},{"time":32032,"text":"for the malaria parasite\nto survive inside the mosquito."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35551,"text":"But that just created another problem."},{"time":38043,"text":"Now that you've got\na malaria-resistant mosquito,"},{"time":40909,"text":"how do you get it to replace\nall the malaria-carrying mosquitos?"},{"time":46107,"text":"There are a couple options,"},{"time":47604,"text":"but plan A was basically to breed up"},{"time":49651,"text":"a bunch of the new\ngenetically-engineered mosquitos"},{"time":52762,"text":"release them into the wild"},{"time":54112,"text":"and hope that they pass on their genes."},{"time":56673,"text":"The problem was that you'd have to release"},{"time":58811,"text":"literally 10 times the number\nof native mosquitos to work."},{"time":63135,"text":"So in a village with 10,000 mosquitos,"},{"time":65246,"text":"you release an extra 100,000."},{"time":68229,"text":"As you might guess,"},{"time":69403,"text":"this was not a very popular strategy\nwith the villagers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72181,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":74963,"text":"Then, last January,\nAnthony James got an email"},{"time":78691,"text":"from a biologist named Ethan Bier."},{"time":81400,"text":"Bier said that he\nand his grad student Valentino Gantz"},{"time":84283,"text":"had stumbled on a tool\nthat could not only guarantee"},{"time":87251,"text":"that a particular genetic trait\nwould be inherited,"},{"time":89949,"text":"but that it would spread\nincredibly quickly."},{"time":92734,"text":"If they were right,\nit would basically solve the problem"},{"time":95424,"text":"that he and James had been\nworking on for 20 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98450,"text":"As a test, they engineered two mosquitos\nto carry the anti-malaria gene"},{"time":103132,"text":"and also this new tool, a gene drive,"},{"time":105315,"text":"which I'll explain in a minute."},{"time":107506,"text":"Finally, they set it up\nso that any mosquitos"},{"time":109863,"text":"that had inherited the anti-malaria gene"},{"time":111825,"text":"wouldn't have the usual white eyes,\nbut would instead have red eyes."},{"time":116682,"text":"That was pretty much just for convenience"},{"time":118756,"text":"so they could tell just at a glance\nwhich was which."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122192,"text":"So they took their two\nanti-malarial, red-eyed mosquitos"},{"time":124973,"text":"and put them in a box\nwith 30 ordinary white-eyed ones,"},{"time":127656,"text":"and let them breed."},{"time":129383,"text":"In two generations, those had produced\n3,800 grandchildren."},{"time":134217,"text":"That is not the surprising part."},{"time":136716,"text":"This is the surprising part:"},{"time":138662,"text":"given that you started\nwith just two red-eyed mosquitos"},{"time":141593,"text":"and 30 white-eyed ones,"},{"time":142951,"text":"you expect mostly white-eyed descendants."},{"time":146514,"text":"Instead, when James opened the box,"},{"time":149562,"text":"all 3,800 mosquitos had red eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153315,"text":"When I asked Ethan Bier about this moment,"},{"time":155379,"text":"he became so excited that he was literally\nshouting into the phone."},{"time":159886,"text":"That's because getting\nonly red-eyed mosquitos"},{"time":162073,"text":"violates a rule that is the absolute\ncornerstone of biology,"},{"time":165045,"text":"Mendelian genetics."},{"time":166912,"text":"I'll keep this quick,"},{"time":168105,"text":"but Mendelian genetics\nsays when a male and a female mate,"},{"time":170893,"text":"their baby inherits half\nof its DNA from each parent."},{"time":173559,"text":"So if our original mosquito was aa\nand our new mosquito is aB,"},{"time":177178,"text":"where B is the anti-malarial gene,"},{"time":179004,"text":"the babies should come out\nin four permutations:"},{"time":181415,"text":"aa, aB, aa, Ba."},{"time":184884,"text":"Instead, with the new gene drive,"},{"time":187197,"text":"they all came out aB."},{"time":189900,"text":"Biologically, that shouldn't\neven be possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192476,"text":"So what happened?"},{"time":194709,"text":"The first thing that happened"},{"time":196177,"text":"was the arrival of a gene-editing tool\nknown as CRISPR in 2012."},{"time":200701,"text":"Many of you have probably\nheard about CRISPR,"},{"time":202835,"text":"so I'll just say briefly that CRISPR\nis a tool that allows researchers"},{"time":206160,"text":"to edit genes very precisely,\neasily and quickly."},{"time":209533,"text":"It does this by harnessing a mechanism\nthat already existed in bacteria."},{"time":213286,"text":"Basically, there's a protein\nthat acts like a scissors"},{"time":215936,"text":"and cuts the DNA,"},{"time":217194,"text":"and there's an RNA molecule\nthat directs the scissors"},{"time":219701,"text":"to any point on the genome you want."},{"time":221443,"text":"The result is basically\na word processor for genes."},{"time":224157,"text":"You can take an entire gene\nout, put one in,"},{"time":226807,"text":"or even edit just a single\nletter within a gene."},{"time":229646,"text":"And you can do it in nearly any species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233328,"text":"OK, remember how I said that gene drives\noriginally had two problems?"},{"time":237835,"text":"The first was that it was hard\nto engineer a mosquito"},{"time":240979,"text":"to be malaria-resistant."},{"time":242390,"text":"That's basically gone now,\nthanks to CRISPR."},{"time":245117,"text":"But the other problem was logistical."},{"time":247307,"text":"How do you get your trait to spread?"},{"time":250196,"text":"This is where it gets clever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252943,"text":"A couple years ago, a biologist\nat Harvard named Kevin Esvelt"},{"time":256569,"text":"wondered what would happen"},{"time":257943,"text":"if you made it so that\nCRISPR inserted not only your new gene"},{"time":261594,"text":"but also the machinery\nthat does the cutting and pasting."},{"time":265233,"text":"In other words, what if CRISPR\nalso copied and pasted itself."},{"time":270145,"text":"You'd end up with a perpetual\nmotion machine for gene editing."},{"time":274458,"text":"And that's exactly what happened."},{"time":277037,"text":"This CRISPR gene drive that Esvelt created"},{"time":279939,"text":"not only guarantees\nthat a trait will get passed on,"},{"time":283606,"text":"but if it's used in the germline cells,"},{"time":286068,"text":"it will automatically copy and paste\nyour new gene"},{"time":288668,"text":"into both chromosomes\nof every single individual."},{"time":291743,"text":"It's like a global search and replace,"},{"time":294164,"text":"or in science terms, it makes\na heterozygous trait homozygous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299045,"text":"So, what does this mean?"},{"time":301680,"text":"For one thing, it means we have\na very powerful,"},{"time":304428,"text":"but also somewhat alarming new tool."},{"time":308576,"text":"Up until now, the fact that gene drives\ndidn't work very well"},{"time":311489,"text":"was actually kind of a relief."},{"time":313425,"text":"Normally when we mess around\nwith an organism's genes,"},{"time":316131,"text":"we make that thing\nless evolutionarily fit."},{"time":318504,"text":"So biologists can make\nall the mutant fruit flies they want"},{"time":321361,"text":"without worrying about it."},{"time":322638,"text":"If some escape, natural selection\njust takes care of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326750,"text":"What's remarkable and powerful\nand frightening about gene drives"},{"time":329997,"text":"is that that will no longer be true."},{"time":333092,"text":"Assuming that your trait does not have\na big evolutionary handicap,"},{"time":336680,"text":"like a mosquito that can't fly,"},{"time":338783,"text":"the CRISPR-based gene drive\nwill spread the change relentlessly"},{"time":342260,"text":"until it is in every single individual\nin the population."},{"time":347101,"text":"Now, it isn't easy to make\na gene drive that works that well,"},{"time":350014,"text":"but James and Esvelt think that we can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353339,"text":"The good news is that this opens\nthe door to some remarkable things."},{"time":357187,"text":"If you put an anti-malarial gene drive"},{"time":359115,"text":"in just 1 percent of Anopheles mosquitoes,"},{"time":361339,"text":"the species that transmits malaria,"},{"time":363488,"text":"researchers estimate that it would spread\nto the entire population in a year."},{"time":368178,"text":"So in a year, you could virtually\neliminate malaria."},{"time":371455,"text":"In practice, we're still a few years out\nfrom being able to do that,"},{"time":375351,"text":"but still, a 1,000 children\na day die of malaria."},{"time":378093,"text":"In a year, that number\ncould be almost zero."},{"time":380966,"text":"The same goes for dengue fever,\nchikungunya, yellow fever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385211,"text":"And it gets better."},{"time":387215,"text":"Say you want to get rid\nof an invasive species,"},{"time":389715,"text":"like get Asian carp\nout of the Great Lakes."},{"time":392434,"text":"All you have to do is release a gene drive"},{"time":394482,"text":"that makes the fish produce\nonly male offspring."},{"time":397386,"text":"In a few generations,\nthere'll be no females left, no more carp."},{"time":401608,"text":"In theory, this means we could restore\nhundreds of native species"},{"time":404711,"text":"that have been pushed to the brink."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407410,"text":"OK, that's the good news,"},{"time":410721,"text":"this is the bad news."},{"time":413070,"text":"Gene drives are so effective"},{"time":415122,"text":"that even an accidental release\ncould change an entire species,"},{"time":418971,"text":"and often very quickly."},{"time":421178,"text":"Anthony James took good precautions."},{"time":423328,"text":"He bred his mosquitos\nin a bio-containment lab"},{"time":425518,"text":"and he also used a species\nthat's not native to the US"},{"time":428130,"text":"so that even if some did escape,"},{"time":429709,"text":"they'd just die off, there'd be nothing\nfor them to mate with."},{"time":432748,"text":"But it's also true that if a dozen\nAsian carp with the all-male gene drive"},{"time":436795,"text":"accidentally got carried\nfrom the Great Lakes back to Asia,"},{"time":440748,"text":"they could potentially wipe out\nthe native Asian carp population."},{"time":445930,"text":"And that's not so unlikely,\ngiven how connected our world is."},{"time":448866,"text":"In fact, it's why we have\nan invasive species problem."},{"time":451912,"text":"And that's fish."},{"time":453428,"text":"Things like mosquitos and fruit flies,"},{"time":456040,"text":"there's literally no way to contain them."},{"time":458024,"text":"They cross borders\nand oceans all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461754,"text":"OK, the other piece of bad news"},{"time":463960,"text":"is that a gene drive\nmight not stay confined"},{"time":466302,"text":"to what we call the target species."},{"time":468556,"text":"That's because of gene flow,"},{"time":470079,"text":"which is a fancy way of saying\nthat neighboring species"},{"time":472700,"text":"sometimes interbreed."},{"time":473972,"text":"If that happens, it's possible\na gene drive could cross over,"},{"time":477147,"text":"like Asian carp could infect\nsome other kind of carp."},{"time":479698,"text":"That's not so bad if your drive\njust promotes a trait, like eye color."},{"time":483437,"text":"In fact, there's a decent\nchance that we'll see"},{"time":485708,"text":"a wave of very weird fruit flies\nin the near future."},{"time":489390,"text":"But it could be a disaster"},{"time":490677,"text":"if your drive is deigned\nto eliminate the species entirely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494351,"text":"The last worrisome thing\nis that the technology to do this,"},{"time":497903,"text":"to genetically engineer an organism\nand include a gene drive,"},{"time":501618,"text":"is something that basically any lab\nin the world can do."},{"time":504976,"text":"An undergraduate can do it."},{"time":507209,"text":"A talented high schooler\nwith some equipment can do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512526,"text":"Now, I'm guessing\nthat this sounds terrifying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515351,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":517581,"text":"Interestingly though,\nnearly every scientist I talk to"},{"time":520495,"text":"seemed to think that gene drives were not\nactually that frightening or dangerous."},{"time":524400,"text":"Partly because they believe\nthat scientists will be"},{"time":527052,"text":"very cautious and responsible\nabout using them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530318,"text":"So far, that's been true."},{"time":532302,"text":"But gene drives also have\nsome actual limitations."},{"time":535022,"text":"So for one thing, they work\nonly in sexually reproducing species."},{"time":538704,"text":"So thank goodness, they can't be used\nto engineer viruses or bacteria."},{"time":542156,"text":"Also, the trait spreads\nonly with each successive generation."},{"time":545370,"text":"So changing or eliminating a population"},{"time":547387,"text":"is practical only if that species\nhas a fast reproductive cycle,"},{"time":550737,"text":"like insects or maybe\nsmall vertebrates like mice or fish."},{"time":554438,"text":"In elephants or people,\nit would take centuries"},{"time":556723,"text":"for a trait to spread\nwidely enough to matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560079,"text":"Also, even with CRISPR, it's not that easy\nto engineer a truly devastating trait."},{"time":566079,"text":"Say you wanted to make a fruit fly"},{"time":567832,"text":"that feeds on ordinary fruit\ninstead of rotting fruit,"},{"time":570411,"text":"with the aim of sabotaging\nAmerican agriculture."},{"time":573068,"text":"First, you'd have to figure out"},{"time":574622,"text":"which genes control\nwhat the fly wants to eat,"},{"time":577418,"text":"which is already a very long\nand complicated project."},{"time":580489,"text":"Then you'd have to alter those genes\nto change the fly's behavior"},{"time":583817,"text":"to whatever you'd want it to be,"},{"time":585379,"text":"which is an even longer\nand more complicated project."},{"time":588204,"text":"And it might not even work,"},{"time":589546,"text":"because the genes\nthat control behavior are complex."},{"time":592064,"text":"So if you're a terrorist\nand have to choose"},{"time":594096,"text":"between starting a grueling\nbasic research program"},{"time":596478,"text":"that will require years of meticulous\nlab work and still might not pan out,"},{"time":600029,"text":"or just blowing stuff up?"},{"time":601400,"text":"You'll probably choose the later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603498,"text":"This is especially true\nbecause at least in theory,"},{"time":605942,"text":"it should be pretty easy\nto build what's called a reversal drive."},{"time":609100,"text":"That's one that basically overwrites\nthe change made by the first gene drive."},{"time":612822,"text":"So if you don't like\nthe effects of a change,"},{"time":615140,"text":"you can just release a second drive\nthat will cancel it out,"},{"time":617997,"text":"at least in theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621374,"text":"OK, so where does this leave us?"},{"time":624604,"text":"We now have the ability\nto change entire species at will."},{"time":629017,"text":"Should we?"},{"time":630552,"text":"Are we gods now?"},{"time":633972,"text":"I'm not sure I'd say that."},{"time":636094,"text":"But I would say this:"},{"time":638329,"text":"first, some very smart people"},{"time":640211,"text":"are even now debating\nhow to regulate gene drives."},{"time":643598,"text":"At the same time,\nsome other very smart people"},{"time":646186,"text":"are working hard to create safeguards,"},{"time":648321,"text":"like gene drives that self-regulate\nor peter out after a few generations."},{"time":652644,"text":"That's great."},{"time":654313,"text":"But this technology still requires\na conversation."},{"time":658059,"text":"And given the nature of gene drives,"},{"time":659813,"text":"that conversation has to be global."},{"time":662131,"text":"What if Kenya wants to use a drive\nbut Tanzania doesn't?"},{"time":665241,"text":"Who decides whether to release\na gene drive that can fly?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":670874,"text":"I don't have the answer to that question."},{"time":673618,"text":"All we can do going forward, I think,"},{"time":675650,"text":"is talk honestly\nabout the risks and benefits"},{"time":678508,"text":"and take responsibility for our choices."},{"time":681817,"text":"By that I mean, not just the choice\nto use a gene drive,"},{"time":685754,"text":"but also the choice not to use one."},{"time":689111,"text":"Humans have a tendency to assume\nthat the safest option"},{"time":692112,"text":"is to preserve the status quo."},{"time":694905,"text":"But that's not always the case."},{"time":697711,"text":"Gene drives have risks,\nand those need to be discussed,"},{"time":701136,"text":"but malaria exists now\nand kills 1,000 people a day."},{"time":704977,"text":"To combat it, we spray pesticides\nthat do grave damage to other species,"},{"time":708565,"text":"including amphibians and birds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711668,"text":"So when you hear about gene drives\nin the coming months,"},{"time":714556,"text":"and trust me, you will\nbe hearing about them,"},{"time":716834,"text":"remember that."},{"time":718402,"text":"It can be frightening to act,"},{"time":720446,"text":"but sometimes, not acting is worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724746,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}